temples.details: The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints has several temples in Canada, with the Cardston Alberta Temple being the first built outside the U.S. and the oldest LDS temple in Canada.
Various traditions, including Jodo Shinshu Buddhism, have temples across Canada, with locations in major cities like Vancouver, Toronto, and smaller communities.
